This is the 1.4 pre-release. The new features compared to genext2fs 1.3 are:

- long options support
- support for SI-style suffixes for some option values.
- --faketime option
- more capable device_table.txt format
- hardlinks support
- sockets support
- big filesystems (>8MB) support
- Solaris 2.x and MacOS X support

There are also various bugfixes and an up-to-date manpage.
Please note that some options have changed, to try to be compatible
with mkfs.jffs2 and mkfs.ext2.

Please test and report bugs to genext2fs-devel@lists.sourceforge.net

